.el .ds Aq '
.TH grex 1  "grex 1.0.0" 
.SH NAME
grex \- grex — nested meta\-repo manager. Pack\-based, agent\-native, Rust\-fast.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBgrex\fR [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-\-plain\fR] [\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR] [\fB\-\-filter\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
grex manages trees of git repositories as a single addressable graph. Each node is a "pack" — a plain git repo plus a `.grex/` contract — and every pack is a meta\-pack by construction (zero children = leaf, N children = orchestrator of N more packs, recursively). One uniform command surface (`sync`, `add`, `rm`, `update`, `status`, `import`, `doctor`, `teardown`, `exec`, `run`, `serve`) operates over the whole graph regardless of depth.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Emit output as JSON
.TP
\fB\-\-plain\fR
Emit plain (non\-color, non\-table) output
.TP
\fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
Show planned actions without executing them
.TP
\fB\-\-filter\fR=\fIFILTER\fR
Filter packs by expression
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
grex\-init(1)
Initialize a grex workspace
.TP
grex\-add(1)
Register and clone a pack
.TP
grex\-rm(1)
Teardown and remove a pack
.TP
grex\-ls(1)
List registered packs
.TP
grex\-status(1)
Report drift vs lockfile
.TP
grex\-sync(1)
Git fetch and pull (recurse by default)
.TP
grex\-update(1)
Sync plus re\-run install on lock change
.TP
grex\-doctor(1)
Run integrity checks
.TP
grex\-serve(1)
Start MCP stdio server
.TP
grex\-import(1)
Import legacy REPOS.json
.TP
grex\-run(1)
Run a named action across packs
.TP
grex\-exec(1)
Execute a shell command in pack context
.TP
grex\-teardown(1)
Tear down a pack tree (reverse of `sync`/`install`)
.TP
grex\-help(1)
Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)
.SH VERSION
v1.0.0
